  "texts": [
    "We observe that over time, users from all groups spend less time revising.",
    "It is worth noting that in the first recipe the users in G A R spent on average more than twice as much time (346 seconds) as the users in G N A R (166 seconds, p <.05), suggesting that the adaptive features prolongated the time users revised the recipes.",
    "Furthermore, when analyzing the number of revisions, we also found significant differences in the overall number of revisions per group (χ 2 (4) = 23.6, p <.001).",
    "In particular, group G A N R revised their recipes more than the rest of the groups (G A R, p <.05; G N A R, p <.001; G N A N R, p <.001; CG, p <.01).",
    "Moreover, we examined the number of revisions per recipe and found that there was also a general declining trend in the average number of revisions (see Fig. 6 (middle))."
  ],
